</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2FB209FF24C9636C69881BCFC8AFD78" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EA5E7314F24C9636C69881BCFC03FD5D" blockId="22.[136,1452,616,1471]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C69881BCFE04FD30" bold="true" box="[189,484,652,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="2DE10897F24C9636C42281BCFC4AFD30" authorityName=", Boissieu" authorityYear="1906" box="[519,938,652,679]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Sanicula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="orthacantha" variety="brevispina">
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C42281BCFD1BFD30" box="[519,763,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sanicula orthacantha</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C51081BCFC4AFD30" box="[821,938,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">brevispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed on Emei Shan, 
<collectingRegion id="2825BDF6F24C9636C2DA81BCFABCFD30" box="[1279,1372,652,678]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="92F63384F24C9636C34D81BCFA4BFD30" box="[1384,1451,652,678]" name="China" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">China</collectingCountry>
(Fig. 17). It grows on slopes or at forest margins at altitude of 
<quantity id="2D19DEF1F24C9636C5648180FC3FFD5D" box="[833,991,688,715]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3825" metricValueMax="2.8649999999999998" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="2382.5" valueMax="2865.0" valueMin="1900.0">1900‒2865 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA5E7314F24C9636C69881E4FC8AFD78" blockId="22.[136,1452,616,1471]" box="[189,874,724,751]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C69881E4FED9FD78" bold="true" box="[189,313,724,750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering and fruiting from later April to July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2FB209FF24C9636C69881C8FB2EFC34" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="EA5E7314F24C9636C69881C8FB2EFC34" blockId="22.[136,1452,616,1471]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C69881C8FE69FC84" bold="true" box="[189,393,760,786]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lectotypification</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="2DE10897F24C9636C7BC81C8FCA0FC84" authorityName="Shan &amp; Liou" authorityYear="1979" box="[409,832,760,787]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Sanicula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="orthacantha" variety="stolonifera">
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C7BC81C8FD6DFC84" box="[409,653,760,786]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sanicula orthacantha</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C4E281C8FCA0FC84" box="[711,832,760,786]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">stolonifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of a single collection 
<emphasis id="D895AF06F24C9636C35381C9FEEDFCA0" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">K.H. Yang 54432</emphasis>
. We have been able to trace 
<specimenCount id="FCE7B89DF24C9636C474802DFD17FCA0" box="[593,759,796,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of the collection at NAS and KUN. As discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="8E700EE5F24C9636C36B802CFF35FCCC" author="McNeill, J." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1112 - 1113" refId="ref14969" refString="McNeill, J. (2014) Holotype specimens and type citations: general issues. Taxon 63: 1112 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 635.7" type="journal article" year="2014">McNeill (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, these sheets all 
<typeStatus id="355ACDB6F24C9636C7B38071FE18FCCD" box="[406,504,833,859]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">syntypes</typeStatus>
as Shan &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="8E700EE5F24C9636C4A58070FCE8FCCC" author="Liou, S. L." box="[640,776,832,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="35 - 63" refId="ref14735" refString="Liou, S. L. (1979) Sanicula L. In: Shan, R. H. &amp; Sheh, M. L. (Eds.) Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol. 55 (1). Science Press, Beijing, pp. 35 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1979">Liou (1979)</bibRefCitation>
